<item>
            <title>[DERBY-253] Client should throw not implemented exception for depricated setUnicodeStream/getUnicodeStream</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-253</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;setUnicodeStream and getUnicodeStream are deprecated API&apos;s &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Network client&lt;br/&gt;
PreparedStatement.setUnicodeStream() and ResultSet.getUnicodeStream() should throw not implemented exceptions rather than trying to handle these calls.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note: The current client implementation of setUnicodeStream() and getUnicodeStream() are broken and can cause unexpected errors&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="32160">DERBY-253</key>
            <summary>Client should throw not implemented exception for depricated setUnicodeStream/getUnicodeStream</summary>
